name: Memorial Medical Center
description: Memorial Medical Center is a full service medical facility with 25 patient beds, 18 doctors on staff and over 200 employees. Over the years we've continued to meet the needs of our community with two extensive renovations and the expansion of several departments and services. We're proud to offer our patients the best of all worlds - quality health services with today's latest technology and care provided by qualified professionals who understand that within each patient is a person. As your community hospital, Memorial Medical Center is committed to your continued good health.  Providing quality care in the Emergency Department, Accredited Level IV Area Trauma Care Facility, is our top priority. When treating emergencies, patients are seen according to the severity of their illness or injury. Those experiencing trouble breathing, chest pain, or severe bleeding will take precedence over those with non life threatening conditions. Your care is our primary concern. If there is anything we can do for you while you are in the emergency department, please let us know. We want to make your experience with Memorial Medical Center is as comfortable as possible. Our on-going commitment to you is to offer you the finest health care services available by people who understand that we treat people, not just patients. Services include:  Cardiopulmonary Diagnostic Imaging Dietary Department Education Services ER Inpatient Services Intensive Care Laboratory Memorial Medical Clinic Medical Surgical Unit Obstetrics Outpatient Clinics Outpatient Services Physical Therapy Program Hope Quality and Safety Infection Prevention Social Services Surgery  One of the goals of Memorial Medical Center is to ensure available and accessible healthcare to the residents of Calhoun County and the surrounding area. Our outpatient services allow individuals access to top quality medical personnel and services without the high cost and inconvenience of a hospital stay. Outpatient Clinics are conveniently located on Memorial Medical Center's second floor. Memorial Medical Clinic has been providing family - centered medical care to Calhoun County since January 2013. Family medicine is the medical specialty that provides continuing and comprehensive health care for the individual and family. The scope of family practice encompasses all ages and genders, each organ system and every disease entity. All our physicians are dedicated to providing medical care that is specifically tailored to your needs and the needs of your family.  If you are in need of financial assistance to cover the cost of your healthcare we services that offer assistance. Calhoun County Indigent Health Care Program (CCIHCP)-Based on eligibility, this program provides basic medical services for the residents of Calhoun County. This temporary assistance includes appointments to local Family Physicians, 3 medications per month (not to exceed $30 total) through HEB Pharmacy & any In-patient or Out-Patient services at Memorial Medical Center. Funds are limited for this assistance. Charity Program is designed to provide free or discounted care to those who have no means, or limited means, to pay for their medical services (Uninsured or Underinsured).

name: Brazos Church Pantry
description: If you are in need of an emergency supply of groceries please come to the pantry and let us help you. The Pantry is here so hungry families can get food in emergency situations.

name: Brazos Interfaith Immigration Network
description: Brazos Immigration seeks to partner with any faith community or organization interested in helping us to fulfill our mission. We partner with local groups to offer citizenship classes and co-host and sponsor informational sessions for immigrants with Catholic Charities Immigration Legal Services, Bryan Independent School District, the United States Citizenship and Immigration Service (USCIS) and the Mexican Consulate. We seek opportunities to build connections and collaborations that strengthen immigrant support.

name: Women's Care Plus
description: Women’s Care Plus supports the health and wellness of women through most phases of their life, from pre-teen to post-menopausal years. We’re a practice designed by women for women that focuses on providing high quality gynecological care in a comfortable environment. Our comprehensive women's care services range from routine wellness exams to addressing difficult hormone disorders, sexual and reproductive health, and many other health issues women face today. Plus, women’s mental health and wellness provided at this location support your complete health.

name: Brazos Valley Council on Alcohol and Substance Abuse
description: Substance Abuse Counseling, Prevention Services. BVCASA is the only non-profit organization in the Brazos Valley with comprehensive youth and adult programs, including state-approved MIP and DWI classes, drug education, substance abuse and tobacco prevention for youth and adults, screening services, outpatient treatment for youth and adults, and residential and outpatient aftercare treatment for adults in the Texas Department of Criminal Justice Substance Abuse Treatment Program

name: HealthPoint
description: HealthPoint seeks to provide evidence-based healthcare utilizing a patient-empowered team approach to achieve individual wellness for all Greater Brazos Valley community members. We do this through a comprehensive approach to your medical needs, including medical and dental services.

name: Habitat For Humanity
description: Habitat works toward our vision by building strength, stability and self-reliance in partnership with families in need of decent and affordable housing. Habitat homeowners help build their own homes alongside volunteers and pay an affordable mortgage

name: Brazos Valley Women's Center
description: From birth control to prenatal nutrition, our professional staff provide a range of services. At BVWC, we strive to offer our patients convenient, high-quality care. Our Care Center is conveniently located in Bryan, Texas. Office Procedures include Obstetric and gynecologic ultrasound - 4D imagining available, Hysteroscopy, Essure permanent sterilization, Endometrial ablation, Colposcopy, LEEP cervical conization, IUD placement and removal, Nexplanon placement and removal, Urodynamic Testing, Pessary Fitting and Placement. Surgeries include Vaginal surgery, Hysteroscopy - diagnostic and operative, Endometrial ablation, Gynecologic laparoscopy, Robotic assisted gynecologic laparoscopy.

name: Counseling and Assessment Clinic
description: The Counseling and Assessment Clinic (CAC) is a psychological service training clinic associated with the Department of Educational Psychology at Texas A&M. All providers at the CAC are trained to provide a variety of psychological services while under the supervision of a Licensed Psychologist. We offer both therapy and assessment services for adults, adolescents, and children in English. Fees are established based on an affordable sliding-scale based on family income and size.

We are the third-largest service provider of free legal aid in the United States. All clients must meet financial and legal status eligibility requirements. Our general income limits change annually and can be found by accessing the US Federal Poverty Guidelines

We house HelpLine and the Suicide Awareness & Prevention Office as well as offering wellness opportunities that include Diversity & Inclusion Programs, Suicide Awareness & Prevention trainings and Wellness/Prevention programs.

name: City of College Station Community Development

The Community Development Division of the Community Services Department is tasked with administering these grant funds through several programs \ndesigned in accordance with the division's goals, federal regulations and input from the City Council.

name: Brazos Valley Financial Fitness Center
description: Gain financial stability by developing healthy financial habits. We provide one-on-one financial coaching and help families and individuals learn more about how to manage money and provide you with lots of financial resources to guide you through making your money work for you! Specifically, we work in the areas of creating an intentional spending plan that includes monthly savings, reducing debt, improving credit and promoting banking relationships. We want you to have all of the tools you need to get the most out of your finances and start saving for the future. Learn how to stay on a budget,manage a checking account, improve your credit ranking, pay off debt, and save for the future.

name: BCS Prenatal Clinic

Other services may also be available; however, other services are provided on an as needed basis to be determined by the nurse practitioners and physician staff who volunteer at the clinic. The clinic offers a comprehensive prenatal program that includes:Prenatal NutritionPhysical/emotional changes during pregnancy and birth Prenatal and postpartum exercise Preparation for labor and birth Parenting skills Breast-feeding Newborn care and feeding

name: Revive Healthcare
description: ReviveHealth provides you the care you want, the medications you need, and supports your well-being with a simple, convenient, and affordable plan that is right for anyone. They offer other plans for people to choose from to meet additional health needs and cover more family members.

name: Regency Integrated Health Services

Our goal is to help residents maximize their mobility and regain their independence.  We provide:  - Residential care - Skilled nursing and medical care - Physical therapy - Occupational therapy - Speech therapy - IV therapy - Wound care - Alzheimer's and dementia care  Regency Integrated Health Services accepts Medicare and Medicaid.

name: Texas Health and Human Services Commission (HHSC)
description: Texas Health and Human Services Commission (HHSC) is the state governmental agency responsible for bringing comprehensive public health services to the citizens of Texas. Personal Care Services (PCS) is a Medicaid benefit that provides assistance with activities of daily living (ADLs), instrumental activities of daily living (IADLs), and health-related functions to help clients with physical, cognitive, or behavioral functional limitations related to a disability, physical or mental illness, or chronic condition.  This program provides:  - Assistance with daily living tasks  Examples of Activities of Daily Living (ADLs):  - Bathing - Eating - Assisting with toileting - Dressing - Assisting with walking  Examples of Instrumental Activities of Daily Living (IADLs):  - Laundry - Meal preparation - Light housework  For more information, or for questions about the PCS benefit, contact the toll-free PCS Client Line at 888-276-0702.

name: Community Attendant Services (CAS)
description: Texas Health and Human Services Commission (HHSC) offers Community Attendant Services to eligible adults and children whose health problems cause them to be functionally limited in performing activities of daily living according to a practitioner's statement of medical need. CAS is a non-technical, medically related personal care service that are provided by an attendant.  This program provides:  - In-home care

name: Harbor Advocacy Center
address: 215 West Railroad Street, Port Lavaca, TX 77979
description: Harbor Advocacy Center offers various services for victims of sexual assault, whether they are an adult or a child. Our services include:  • 24-hour Crisis Hotline answered by trained staff and volunteers • Medical, legal and law accompaniments 24 hours a day • Counseling • Assistance with Crime Victim Compensation • Transportation to the hospital, court and/or police department or sheriff's department • Crisis Intervention • Support and information for family members and friends of victim  In addition, our center is also able to provide assistance on behalf of a child or adult survivors of sexual violence with third parties, such as schools, employers, law enforcement agencies, etc. There is no appointment necessary for immediate face to face crisis intervention and advocacy services during normal business hours. If you feel you are in immediate need of help, please don't hesitate to call our 24 hour crisis hotline at 361-552-HELP(4357).

description: This is the prison in DeWitt, TX. Visitors are allowed on Saturdays and Sundays from 8:00 AM - 5:00 PM for 2 hours, and must stop right at 5:00 PM. Inmates are allowed one visit each weekend. Visitors will need proper identification and can bring up to twenty dollars in quarters stored in a clear Ziploc bag to use in the visiting room at the vending machine. Paper money is not allowed to be sure to exchange for coins before arriving. Contact the facility before arriving to ensure that the inmate is still there and that visitation is possible.

It is a tax exempt organization and has been in operation for 34 years. Clients can get assistance with paying for and picking up prescriptions, paying for doctor or dentist appointments, gas for transportation to doctor appointments, and assistance with rent and utilities once every six months.

name: Edna Police Department

The agency is comprised of ten full time sworn officers. The chief of police, who is appointed and directed by the city manager, directs two Lieutenant Detectives, one Sergeant/School Resource Officer, and six patrol officers. The agency has two designated reserve officer positions. The police chief also directs one animal control officer and one records clerk.

description: The Official WIC program is available to low to moderate income pregnant women, recently delivered women, breastfeeding women, infants, and children up to age 5 who are at nutrition risk. name: The Purple Door - Beeville Office
description: The Purple Door is a nonprofit organization located in Coastal Bend College. They provide services individuals affected by domestic violence and/or sexual assault. Services include counseling, legal advocacy. advocacy, support groups, shelter, and a crisis hotline. Those seeking emergency shelter are admitted on a case-by-case basis and The Purple Door does not turn away any survivors nor is there a time limit for staying as long as they are compliant. There are 15 bedrooms and children are also permitted to stay with their guardian. Breakfast, lunch, dinner, and snacks are provided, and dietary needs are able to be accomodated for. There are services for children to help them feel safe and there is a donation room with clothing, toiletries, shoes, diapers, and other needed items. The crisis hotline is (361) - 881 - 8888 or 1 - (800) - 580 - 4878. If you have any questions call the number below this description.

name: Beeville Vineyard
description: The Beeville Vineyard is a nonprofit faith-based organization that provides clothing and household items, emergency shelter, fans and heaters, rental assistance, prescription assistance, utility assistance, and transportation assistance to the residents of Bee County with low incomes, the elderly, the sick, and those going through difficult times. Residents are allowed to shop for clothing and household items once a month. Assistance with eviction notices and utility disconnections are available every 2 years with provided documentation. Beeville Vineyard also provides emergency food every 30 days for residents with no documentation required to qualify. Shopping for clothing, household items, and emergency food can occur between 9:00 AM - 11:30 AM and 1:00 PM - 2:30 PM. The documents required to open a file include current photo ID, a utility bill (water, gas, or electricity) with name and address, if there is no utility bill then a copy of their lease, current pay stub or award letter for income, and dependent children under 18 years old need a social security card or proof of custody. These documents can be emailed to vineyarddirector@gmail.com, texted to (361) - 434 - 0186, or faxed to (361) - 358 - 5181.

name: Serenity Counseling Services
description: Serenity Counseling Services provides counseling and telehealth for children, adolescents, and teenagers, individual counseling for adults, family counseling, marriage/couples counseling, group counseling, psychoeducation, trainings, and presentations, and emotional intelligence camp for kids. They are focused on helping with anxiety, depression, ADHD/ADD, self-esteem, grief, boundaries, co-dependency, financial struggles, parenting, coping skills, emotional intelligence, etc. They accept insurance from Blue Cross Blue Shield, United Healthcare, Christus Spohn Health Network, Cigna, Beacon, Medicaid (Driscoll Health Plan, Superior Health Plan, and United Healthcare Community Plan), and Medicare with billing soon in Spring 2024. If you have any questions about services or finances call the number below this description. Specific services include adult mental health, youth and family services, intellectual and developmental disabilities services, family partner services, CPCC Integration Program (primary healthcare services - adult primary care, women's services, laboratory services and education, pharmacy services, enabling services, including enrollment and referral to state programs like CHIP or medicaid, eligibility and enrollment, and preventative care), Texas Correctional Office on Offenders with Medical or Mental Impairments (TCOOMMI), veteran services, substance use services, and crisis services. description: Nueces County Community Action Agency - 22nd St. is a social services organization that seeks to help rid the causes of poverty for those in Nueces County. They provide programs such as case management, tuition assistance, affordable housing, utility assistance, weatherization, home preservation and modification, information and referral resources, etc. The applications who are awarded the service will be chosen based on a first come first serve basis with priority given to the elderly (greater than 60 years old), very young (children 5 years or younger), and disabled populations.
